            <head>A
Short <normalised orig="Catechisme" auto="true">Catechism</normalised>.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. WHat ought to be the <normalised orig="Chiefe" auto="true">Chief</normalised><lb/>
and <normalised orig="continuall" auto="true">continual</normalised> care of <normalised orig="euerie" auto="true">every</normalised><lb/>
man in this life?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. To <normalised orig="glorifie" auto="true">glorify</normalised> God,<lb/>
and <normalised orig="saue" auto="true">save</normalised> his <normalised orig="soule" auto="true">soul</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Whence <choice ana="typeset-error">
                     <sic/>
                     <corr>must</corr>
                  </choice> wee take direction<lb/>
to <normalised orig="attaine" auto="true">attain</normalised> hereunto?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Out of the word of God alone.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What call you the word of God?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. The holy Scripture immediately<lb/>
inspired, which is contained in the<lb/>
<normalised orig="Bookes" auto="true">Books</normalised> of the Old and New Testament.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are the <normalised orig="Bookes" auto="true">Books</normalised> of the Old<lb/>
Testament?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Moses, and the Prophets.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Which are the <normalised orig="Bookes" auto="true">Books</normalised> of the new Testament?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            
            <fw type="pageNum">A3</fw>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Matthew, <normalised orig="Marke" auto="true">Mark</normalised>, Luke, and the<lb/>
rest, as they follow in our Bibles.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How may it <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> <normalised orig="proued" auto="true">proved</normalised> that those<lb/>
<normalised orig="Bookes" auto="true">Books</normalised> are the word of God, immediately inspired<lb/>
by the Holy Ghost to the Prophets<lb/>
and Apostles?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By the <normalised orig="testimonie" auto="true">testimony</normalised> of the Church,<lb/>
<normalised orig="constancie" auto="true">constancy</normalised> of the Saints, miracles<lb/>
wrought to <normalised orig="confirme" auto="true">confirm</normalised> the truth, and the<lb/>
<normalised orig="Antiquitie" auto="true">Antiquity</normalised> thereof.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How else?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By the stile, <normalised orig="efficacie" auto="true">efficacy</normalised>, <normalised orig="sweete" auto="true">sweet</normalised><lb/>
consent, admirable doctrine, excellent<lb/>
end, and the <normalised orig="witnesse" auto="true">witness</normalised> of the Scripture<lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*t</sic>
                     <corr>it</corr>
                  </choice> <normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised><lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. These reasons may <normalised orig="conuince" auto="true">convince</normalised> any, be he<lb/>
<normalised orig="neuer" auto="true">never</normalised> so obstinate; but are they sufficient to<lb/>
                  <pb n="2"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="perswade" auto="true">persuade</normalised> the heart thereof?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. No: the <normalised orig="testimonie" auto="true">testimony</normalised> of the Spirit<lb/>
is necessary; and <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> all-sufficient<lb/>
for this purpose.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are the properties of the Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. It is of <normalised orig="Diuine" auto="true">Divine</normalised> <normalised orig="authoritie" auto="true">authority</normalised>, the rule<lb/>
of faith and Manners, <normalised orig="necessarie" auto="true">necessary</normalised>,<lb/>
pure, perfect, and <normalised orig="plaine" auto="true">plain</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. For what end was the <choice ana="typeset-error">
                     <sic/>
                     <corr>Scripture</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
written?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. To teach, instruct, <normalised orig="conuince" auto="true">convince</normalised>, correct,<lb/>
and comfort. 2. Tim .3. 16.17 <notvariant>Rom</notvariant><lb/>
.15.4.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q <normalised orig="Doth" auto="false">Does</normalised> the knowledge of the <choice ana="print-error">
                     <sic><notvariant>Scripres</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>Scriptures</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
belong <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> all men?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Yes, all men are not only allowed,<lb/>
but exhorted, and commanded to read,<lb/>
<normalised orig="heare" auto="true">hear</normalised>, and <normalised orig="vnderstand" auto="true">understand</normalised> the Scriptures.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. The Scriptures were written in<lb/>
Hebrew and <normalised orig="Greeke" auto="true">Greek</normalised>, how then shall all<lb/>
men read, and <normalised orig="vnderstand" auto="true">understand</normalised> them?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. They ought to be <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>transla</notvariant>*ed</sic>
                     <corr>translated</corr>
                  </choice> into<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum">A4</fw>
                  <pb n="3"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="knowne" auto="true">known</normalised> tongues, and <normalised orig="interperted" auto="false">interpreted</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What <normalised orig="doth" auto="false">does</normalised> the Scripture especially<lb/>
teach <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. The <normalised orig="sauing" auto="true">saving</normalised> knowledge of God,<lb/>
and <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised> Christ.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How may it <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> <normalised orig="prooued" auto="true">proved</normalised> that there<lb/>
is a God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By the <normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised>, and wonders<lb/>
which are <normalised orig="seene" auto="true">seen</normalised>, the <normalised orig="testimonie" auto="true">testimony</normalised> of conscience,<lb/>
the powers of the <normalised orig="soule" auto="true">soul</normalised>, and the<lb/>
practises of Satan.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How else?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By the consent of Nations, defence<lb/>
of the Church, support, and comfort<lb/>
of the godly, but principally by the<lb/>
Scriptures,<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is God?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. He is a Spirit, <normalised orig="hauing" auto="true">having</normalised> his being<lb/>
of <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised>,<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How many Gods be there?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <normalised orig="Onely" auto="true">Only</normalised> one God, and three persons,<lb/>
the Father, <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised>, and holy Ghost.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the <normalised orig="propertie" auto="true">property</normalised> of the Father?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. To <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> of <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised>, and to beget<lb/>
his <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the <normalised orig="propertie" auto="true">property</normalised> of the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. To <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> begotten of the Father.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the <normalised orig="propertie" auto="true">property</normalised> of the Holy<lb/>
Ghost?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. To proceed from the Father, and<lb/>
the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. The nature of God is infinite and<lb/>
incomprehensible, how then may we <normalised orig="conceiue" auto="true">conceive</normalised><lb/>
of him?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By his properties, and by his<lb/>
<normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are his properties?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. He is most wise, strong, good,<lb/>
gracious, <normalised orig="iust" auto="true">just</normalised>, <normalised orig="mercifull" auto="true">merciful</normalised>, perfect,<lb/>
blessed, and <normalised orig="glorius" auto="false">glorious</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are his <normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. They are three, Decree, Creation,<lb/>
and <normalised orig="Prouidence" auto="true">Providence</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the Decree?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. That whereby God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> from<lb/>
<normalised orig="eternitie" auto="true">eternity</normalised> set <normalised orig="downe" auto="true">down</normalised> with <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="whatsoeuer" auto="true">whatsoever</normalised> shall come to <normalised orig="passe" auto="true">pass</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is Creation?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. That <normalised orig="wherby" auto="true">whereby</normalised> God made all things<lb/>
of nothing, in six <normalised orig="dayes" auto="true">days</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. In what <normalised orig="forme" auto="true">form</normalised> or manner were all<lb/>
things created?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. In an <normalised orig="execellent" auto="false">excellent</normalised> order, and exceeding<lb/>
good.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. For what end did God make all<lb/>
things?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. For the praise of this power, <normalised orig="goodnesse" auto="true">goodness</normalised>,<lb/>
<normalised orig="wisdome" auto="true">wisdom</normalised>, perfection, and <normalised orig="freedome" auto="true">freedom</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is <normalised orig="prouidence" auto="true">providence</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. That whereby God <normalised orig="doth" auto="false">does</normalised> <normalised orig="preserue" auto="true">preserve</normalised><lb/>
and <normalised orig="gouerne" auto="true">govern</normalised> all things with all<lb/>
their actions.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are the <normalised orig="speciall" auto="true">special</normalised> creatures made,<lb/>
<normalised orig="preserued" auto="true">preserved</normalised>, and <normalised orig="gouerned" auto="true">governed</normalised> by the Lord?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Angels, and men.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="6"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What was the state of <choice ana="print-error">
                     <sic><notvariant>aman</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>a man</corr>
                  </choice> by creation<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <normalised orig="Marueilous" auto="true">Marvelous</normalised>, holy, and happy<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Why say you that man was holy?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Because he was created after the<lb/>
image of God, in knowledge, <normalised orig="righteousnesse" auto="true">righteousness</normalised>,<lb/>
and true <normalised orig="holinesse" auto="true">holiness</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Wherein did mans <normalised orig="happines" auto="true">happiness</normalised> consist?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. In the <normalised orig="inioying" auto="true">enjoying</normalised> of <normalised orig="sweete" auto="true">sweet</normalised> peace<lb/>
and communion with God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What further <normalised orig="priuiledges" auto="true">privileges</normalised> did Man<lb/>
<normalised orig="enioy" auto="true">enjoy</normalised> in this state of <normalised orig="innocencie" auto="true">innocence</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. He was placed in Paradise, had liberty<lb/>
to <normalised orig="eate" auto="true">eat</normalised> of <normalised orig="euery" auto="true">every</normalised> tree of the garden,<lb/>
except the tree of <choice ana="print-error">
                     <sic><notvariant>knowlede</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>knowledge</corr>
                  </choice> of good<lb/>
and <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised>, and was made ruler of <normalised orig="al" auto="true">all</normalised> earthly<lb/>
Creatures.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Were these things bestowed <normalised orig="vpon" auto="true">upon</normalised><lb/>
man that he might <normalised orig="liue" auto="true">live</normalised> as he list?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. No: but that he might <normalised orig="serue" auto="true">serve</normalised> the<lb/>
Lord his maker who therefore <normalised orig="gaue" auto="true">gave</normalised> man<lb/>
a law, binding him <normalised orig="alwayes" auto="true">always</normalised> to perfect<lb/>
obedience, and a special <normalised orig="commandement" auto="true">commandment</normalised><lb/>
to <normalised orig="trie" auto="true">try</normalised> him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What was that <normalised orig="speciall" auto="true">special</normalised> <normalised orig="co~mandement" auto="false">commandment</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="7"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <quote type="biblical" ana="Gen 2.17">Of the tree of knowledge of good<lb/>
and <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised>, thou shalt not <normalised orig="eate" auto="true">eat</normalised>: for in the<lb/>
day that thou <notvariant>eatest</notvariant> thereof, thou shalt<lb/>
die the death.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Death wee <normalised orig="heare" auto="true">hear</normalised> was <normalised orig="threatned" auto="true">threatened</normalised> if<lb/>
he disobeyed, what promise was made to<lb/>
encourage him to his <normalised orig="dutie" auto="true">duty</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. The continuance both of <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised>,<lb/>
