               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Did man continue in that good estate?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. No: but he fell from God, through<lb/>
the <normalised orig="inticement" auto="true">enticement</normalised> of Satan.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How did he fall?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. By sinning wilfully against God,<lb/>
transgressing his Law:<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What was the <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> he did commit?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. The eating of the forbidden fruit.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Did all mankind <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> in Adam?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Yes for wee were all in his <normalised orig="loynes" auto="true">loins</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the state of all men by reason Adams fall?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. They are dead in sin, and <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>bonds*<notvariant>ues</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="bondslaues" auto="true">bondslaves</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
of Satan.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How <normalised orig="doth" auto="false">does</normalised> that <normalised orig="appeare" auto="true">appear</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="8"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. In that they are altogether <normalised orig="vnable" auto="true">unable</normalised><lb/>
to good, and prone to <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised> continually.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What fruits <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> proceed from this<lb/>
<normalised orig="originall" auto="true">original</normalised> corruption?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <normalised orig="Euill" auto="true">Evil</normalised> thoughts, words, &amp; works.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Are all the actions of <normalised orig="naturall" auto="true">natural</normalised> men<lb/>
<normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised> continually?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Yes, for they <normalised orig="faile" auto="true">fail</normalised> in many things,<lb/>
and therefore as they come from them,<lb/>
they are odious <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
